<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<!-- viewport-fit=cover is required for env(safe-area-inset-*) to report real
     values on notched iPhones; without it the add button sits under the notch. -->
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, viewport-fit=cover">
<meta name="theme-color" content="#1f3bff">
<!-- PWA: installable to the home screen, opens full-screen, works offline.
     All paths are relative so they resolve under the /nice-events/ project path. -->
<link rel="manifest" href="manifest.webmanifest">
<link rel="icon" href="favicon-32.png" sizes="32x32">
<link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="apple-touch-icon.png">
<meta name="apple-mobile-web-app-capable" content="yes">
<meta name="mobile-web-app-capable" content="yes">
<meta name="apple-mobile-web-app-status-bar-style" content="default">
<meta name="apple-mobile-web-app-title" content="Nice Events">
<title>{{ title }} — events in Nice &amp; the 06</title>
<meta name="description" content="Vide-greniers, milongas, concerts, exhibitions, meetups and pop-ups across Nice and the Alpes-Maritimes. Updated daily.">
<meta property="og:title" content="{{ title }}">
<meta property="og:description" content="Everything on in Nice and the 06 — updated daily.">
<meta property="og:type" content="website">
<style>
:root{color-scheme:light;--ink:#0e0e0e;--paper:#f4f2ed;--accent:#1f3bff;--muted:#7d7970;--rule:#d8d4cb}
*{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}
body{background:var(--paper);color:var(--ink);font-family:"Helvetica Neue",Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:15px;line-height:1.45;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased}
.wrap{max-width:1180px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 28px 80px}
a{color:var(--accent)}
.hero{padding:44px 0 0}
/* padding-right clears the fixed add-event button (52px wide at right:24px = 76px
   of occupied gutter). Without it the button sits on top of "· 5 SOURCES". */
.eyebrow{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:baseline;gap:16px;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);border-bottom:1px solid var(--ink);padding-bottom:10px;padding-right:76px}
.eyebrow b{color:var(--ink);font-weight:600}
/* A button that reads as a text link — for "About" in the eyebrow and footer. */
.linklike{border:0;background:none;padding:0;margin:0;min-height:0;font:inherit;
  letter-spacing:inherit;text-transform:inherit;color:var(--muted);cursor:pointer;
  text-decoration:underline;text-underline-offset:2px}
.linklike:hover{background:none;color:var(--accent)}
/* About dialog reads as prose, not a form. */
.about-body p{margin:0 0 14px;font-size:15.5px;line-height:1.6;max-width:60ch}
.about-body p:last-child{margin-bottom:0}
.about-body a{color:var(--accent)}
.about-body .sign{font-weight:600;color:var(--ink)}
h1{font-size:clamp(58px,12.5vw,168px);line-height:.83;letter-spacing:-.05em;font-weight:800;margin:26px 0 0;text-transform:uppercase}
h1 em{font-style:normal;color:var(--accent)}
.standfirst{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:40px;margin:30px 0 0;padding-bottom:28px}
.standfirst p{font-size:17px;line-height:1.4;max-width:46ch}
.stats{display:flex;gap:38px;align-self:end;justify-content:flex-end}
.stat b{display:block;font-size:40px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:-.03em;line-height:1}
.stat span{font-size:10.5px;letter-spacing:.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted)}
.marquee{border-top:1px solid var(--ink);border-bottom:1px solid var(--ink);overflow:hidden;white-space:nowrap;padding:11px 0;margin-bottom:34px;background:var(--ink);color:var(--paper)}
.marquee-inner{display:inline-block;animation:slide 38s linear infinite}
.marquee span{font-size:12.5px;letter-spacing:.2em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:0 16px}
.marquee span::after{content:"◆";margin-left:32px;color:var(--accent)}
@keyframes slide{from{transform:translateX(0)}to{transform:translateX(-50%)}}
@media(prefers-reduced-motion:reduce){.marquee-inner{animation:none}}
.bar{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;align-items:center;margin-bottom:16px}
/* "Online too" — a real control, so it gets the same box as the selects rather
   than floating naked next to them. */
.chk{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:7px;white-space:nowrap;cursor:pointer;
     border:1px solid var(--ink);padding:9px 11px;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;
     letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;user-select:none}
.chk:hover{background:#e8e5de}
.chk input{width:14px;height:14px;margin:0;padding:0;accent-color:var(--accent);cursor:pointer}
input,select,textarea{font:inherit;font-size:14.5px;padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid var(--ink);border-radius:0;background:transparent;color:var(--ink)}
input[type=search]{flex:1;min-width:190px}
input:focus,select:focus,textarea:focus{outline:2px solid var(--accent);outline-offset:-2px}
/* Equal columns — NOT flex:1 with flex-wrap. Under flex-wrap each ROW shares the
   width among only the items that landed on it, so the final row of 2 rendered
   at 50% each ("MARKETS & FÊTES" / "OTHER" stretched to half the page) while the
   row above sat at 25%. A grid gives every cell the same width regardless of how
   many fall on the last row.
   4 and 3 both divide the 12 categories exactly, so there's never a ragged row.
   The container draws top+left; each cell draws its own right+bottom. That way
   the outer edges are single hairlines, not doubled. */
.cats{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);border:1px solid var(--ink);border-right:0;border-bottom:0;margin-bottom:22px}
.cat{display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;text-align:center;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:10px 6px;cursor:pointer;border-right:1px solid var(--ink);border-bottom:1px solid var(--ink);user-select:none;white-space:nowrap;font-weight:600}
.cat:hover{background:#e8e5de}
.cat.on{background:var(--ink);color:var(--paper)}
.cat i{font-style:normal;opacity:.5;margin-left:5px;font-weight:400}
button{font:inherit;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;font-weight:600;padding:9px 16px;border:1px solid var(--ink);background:transparent;color:var(--ink);cursor:pointer}
button:hover{background:var(--ink);color:var(--paper)}
button.primary{background:var(--accent);border-color:var(--accent);color:#fff}
.tally{font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:4px}
.daymark{display:flex;align-items:baseline;gap:14px;margin:34px 0 0;padding-bottom:7px;border-bottom:2px solid var(--ink)}
.daymark b{font-size:22px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:-.02em}
.daymark span{font-size:10.5px;letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted)}
.row{display:grid;grid-template-columns:46px 1fr 210px 120px;gap:18px;align-items:baseline;padding:15px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule)}
.row:hover{background:#e9e6df}
.idx{font-size:11px;color:var(--muted);font-variant-numeric:tabular-nums}
.ttl{font-size:19px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:-.015em;line-height:1.2}
.ttl a{color:var(--ink);text-decoration:none}
.ttl a:hover{color:var(--accent);text-decoration:underline;text-underline-offset:3px}
.sub{font-size:12.5px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:4px}
.where{font-size:12.5px}
.where b{display:block;font-weight:600}
.where span{color:var(--muted)}
.kind{font-size:9.5px;letter-spacing:.13em;text-transform:uppercase;font-weight:700;text-align:right;color:var(--muted)}
.pill{display:inline-block;font-size:9px;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;font-weight:700;padding:2px 6px;margin-right:5px;vertical-align:2px;background:var(--accent);color:#fff}
.pill.out{background:transparent;color:var(--muted);border:1px solid var(--rule)}
/* Run-length sticker for exhibitions and other multi-day events. */
.pill.run{background:transparent;color:var(--accent);border:1px solid var(--accent)}
/* Discrete per-event icon buttons (share, add-to-calendar). Reset the global
   button chrome so they're just muted icons, not bordered boxes. */
.sharebtn,.calbtn,.cardbtn{border:0;background:none;padding:5px;margin-left:2px;color:var(--muted);
  cursor:pointer;line-height:0;vertical-align:-3px;min-height:0}
.sharebtn:hover,.calbtn:hover,.cardbtn:hover{background:none;color:var(--accent)}
.sharebtn svg,.calbtn svg,.cardbtn svg{display:block}
.sharebtn[data-copied]{color:#0a7a3f}
.cardbtn[data-busy]{color:var(--accent);opacity:.6}
/* A shared event, opened via ?e=… — highlighted in blue and scrolled to. */
.row.hl{background:rgba(31,59,255,.10);box-shadow:inset 3px 0 0 var(--accent)}
.sec{margin-top:76px}
.sechead{display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:20px;border-top:2px solid var(--ink);padding-top:14px;margin-bottom:24px}
.secnum{font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.16em;color:var(--muted);padding-top:9px}
.sechead h2{font-size:clamp(30px,4.6vw,54px);font-weight:800;letter-spacing:-.035em;line-height:.95;text-transform:uppercase}
.sechead p{font-size:13.5px;color:var(--muted);max-width:40ch;margin-left:auto;padding-top:8px}
.form{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:10px}
.f-full{grid-column:1/-1}.f-half{grid-column:span 2}
label{display:block;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:5px;font-weight:600}
label i{font-style:normal;text-transform:none;letter-spacing:0;font-weight:400;opacity:.6}
.form input,.form select,.form textarea{width:100%}
.callout{border-left:3px solid var(--accent);background:rgba(31,59,255,.05);padding:14px 16px;font-size:15px;line-height:1.5;color:#4a463f;margin-bottom:22px;max-width:56ch}
.callout b{color:var(--ink)}
/* Snap-a-flyer */
.snap{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-bottom:20px}
.snap-btn{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;cursor:pointer;font-size:13.5px;
  background:var(--accent);color:#fff;border:1px solid var(--accent);
  font-size:12px;letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase;font-weight:600;
  padding:11px 16px;min-height:44px}
.snap-btn:hover{background:var(--ink);border-color:var(--ink)}
.snap-msg{font-size:14px;color:var(--muted);flex:1;min-width:180px}
.snap-msg.busy{color:var(--accent)}
.snap-msg.done{color:#0a7a3f}

/* Add-event: blue square, white plus, pinned top-right. Opens the form as a
   dialog so it stays out of the way until wanted. */
.addbtn{
  position:fixed;top:24px;right:24px;z-index:50;
  width:52px;height:52px;padding:0;border:0;border-radius:0;
  background:var(--accent);color:#fff;cursor:pointer;
  display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;
  transition:transform .12s ease, background .12s ease;
}
.addbtn:hover{background:var(--ink);color:#fff;transform:scale(1.06)}
.addbtn:focus-visible{outline:3px solid var(--ink);outline-offset:3px}
.addbtn svg{width:22px;height:22px;display:block}
/* max-height + a scrollable body are load-bearing, not polish. Without them a
   dialog taller than the window overflows it and the browser gives you no way to
   reach the bottom — the Submit button was being cut off the screen entirely.
   The head stays put (flex:none) and only .dlg-body scrolls. */
dialog{
  border:1px solid var(--ink);border-radius:0;padding:0;background:var(--paper);
  color:var(--ink);max-width:760px;width:calc(100% - 40px);
  max-height:calc(100dvh - 40px);margin:auto;
  display:flex;flex-direction:column;
}
dialog:not([open]){display:none}
dialog::backdrop{background:rgba(14,14,14,.55)}
/* A little pop on open — the form springs in rather than blinking into place. */
@keyframes dlgpop{from{opacity:0;transform:translateY(10px) scale(.97)}to{opacity:1;transform:none}}
@keyframes bdfade{from{opacity:0}to{opacity:1}}
dialog[open]{animation:dlgpop .2s cubic-bezier(.2,.85,.25,1)}
dialog[open]::backdrop{animation:bdfade .2s ease}
@media(prefers-reduced-motion:reduce){dialog[open],dialog[open]::backdrop{animation:none}}
.dlg-head{
  display:flex;align-items:flex-start;justify-content:space-between;gap:16px;
  padding:22px 24px 14px;border-bottom:2px solid var(--ink);flex:none;
}
.dlg-head h2{font-size:34px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:-.035em;line-height:.95;text-transform:uppercase}
.dlg-head p{font-size:15px;color:var(--ink);margin-top:8px;max-width:40ch}
.dlg-x{width:34px;height:34px;padding:0;border:1px solid var(--ink);background:transparent;
  font-size:17px;line-height:1;cursor:pointer;flex:none}
.dlg-x:hover{background:var(--ink);color:var(--paper)}
.dlg-body{padding:20px 24px 24px;overflow-y:auto;flex:1}
@media(max-width:860px){.addbtn{top:12px;right:12px;width:46px;height:46px}}
.err{color:#b00020;font-size:12.5px;margin-top:8px}
.ok{color:#0a7a3f;font-size:12.5px;margin-top:8px}
.foot{margin-top:70px;border-top:1px solid var(--ink);padding-top:16px;font-size:11.5px;color:var(--muted)}
.foot a{color:var(--muted)}
.empty{padding:60px 0;text-align:center;color:var(--muted)}
/* ---------------- tablet ---------------- */
@media(max-width:860px){
 .row{grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:4px}
 .idx{display:none}
 .standfirst{grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:22px}
 .stats{justify-content:flex-start}
 .form{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}
 .cats{grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr)}   /* 12 / 3 = 4 full rows */
 .eyebrow{padding-right:64px}                 /* 46px button at right:12px */
}

/* ---------------- phone ----------------
   Notes on the non-obvious bits:
   - inputs go to 16px: anything smaller makes iOS Safari zoom the whole page
     on focus, and it never zooms back out. This is the single most common
     mobile form bug.
   - the category tabs become a horizontal scroll strip. As a wrapped grid,
     12 categories = 6 rows of chrome before you see a single event.
   - safe-area insets keep the button clear of the notch / Dynamic Island.
   - the dialog goes near-fullscreen; a centred modal on a 390px screen is
     just a cramped box.                                                     */
@media(max-width:600px){
 body{font-size:16px}
 .wrap{padding:0 16px 64px}

 .hero{padding:14px 0 0}
 /* Mobile is tight and consulted on the go — drop the decorative eyebrow and the
    intro paragraph so the actual events start higher up the screen. */
 .eyebrow{display:none}
 h1{font-size:clamp(46px,15vw,74px);margin-top:6px;letter-spacing:-.04em}
 .standfirst{margin-top:16px;padding-bottom:16px;gap:18px}
 .standfirst p{display:none}
 .stats{gap:24px}
 .stat b{font-size:30px}
 .stat span{font-size:9px;letter-spacing:.1em}

 .marquee{padding:9px 0;margin-bottom:22px}
 .marquee span{font-size:10.5px;letter-spacing:.16em;padding:0 12px}
 .marquee span::after{margin-left:22px}

 /* Filters in three tidy rows: search (full), town+date (half each), then
    "Online too" + Reset sharing the last row. Cramming all five controls into
    one wrapping line was the awkward part. */
 .bar{gap:7px;margin-bottom:12px}
 input[type=search]{flex:1 0 100%;min-width:0}
 #town,#when{flex:1 1 calc(50% - 4px);min-width:0}
 .chk{flex:1 1 auto;justify-content:center;white-space:nowrap;min-height:44px}
 #reset{flex:0 0 auto}
 input,select,textarea{font-size:16px;padding:11px 12px}   /* 16px: no iOS zoom */
 button{padding:11px 14px;min-height:44px}                  /* 44px touch target */

 /* Category filter: WRAPPING chips, so all 12 are visible and tappable at once.
    The old horizontal scroll strip hid most categories off the right edge with
    no hint they were there — that was the "awkward filters" on mobile. */
 .cats{
   display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:6px;border:0;margin-bottom:16px;
 }
 .cat{
   flex:0 0 auto;border:1px solid var(--ink);padding:8px 11px;
   font-size:10.5px;min-height:38px;
   display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;
 }

 .daymark{margin-top:26px;gap:9px}
 .daymark b{font-size:19px}
 .daymark span{font-size:9.5px}

 .row{padding:16px 0;gap:4px}                    /* more breathing room between events */
 .ttl{font-size:20px;line-height:1.3}            /* bigger, easier to read while scrolling */
 .ttl a{
   /* Bigger tap area without visibly changing the layout. */
   display:inline-block;padding:2px 0;
 }
 /* Clamp the long museum blurbs to 2 lines so the list stays scannable — the
    full text is one tap away on the source page. */
 .sub{font-size:14px;line-height:1.45;margin-top:5px;display:-webkit-box;-webkit-line-clamp:2;-webkit-box-orient:vertical;overflow:hidden}
 /* Town and venue collapse onto one line. The separator hangs off the venue,
    not the town — otherwise an event with no venue renders "Nice · " with a
    dangling dot. */
 .where{font-size:13.5px;margin-top:2px}
 .where b{display:inline}
 .where span{display:inline}
 .where span:not(:empty)::before{content:" · ";color:var(--muted)}
 /* Category label moves inline under the title rather than eating a column. */
 .kind{display:block;text-align:left;font-size:10px;margin-top:3px}

 .addbtn{top:max(10px,env(safe-area-inset-top));right:max(10px,env(safe-area-inset-right));
         width:44px;height:44px}
 .addbtn svg{width:19px;height:19px}

 dialog{
   width:100%;max-width:none;height:100dvh;max-height:100dvh;
   margin:0;border:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;
 }
 dialog[open]{position:fixed;inset:0}
 .dlg-head{padding:16px 16px 12px;padding-top:max(16px,env(safe-area-inset-top))}
 .dlg-head h2{font-size:24px}
 .dlg-head p{font-size:12px}
 .dlg-x{width:44px;height:44px;font-size:19px}
 .dlg-body{padding:16px;overflow-y:auto;flex:1;
           padding-bottom:max(16px,env(safe-area-inset-bottom))}
 .form{grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:12px}
 .f-half,.f-full{grid-column:1/-1}
 .form button{width:100%}
 .form .f-full[style]{flex-direction:column;align-items:stretch!important}

 .callout{padding-left:12px;font-size:12.5px}
 .foot{margin-top:44px;font-size:11px}
}

/* Landscape phone: don't let a 100dvh dialog trap the form. */
@media(max-width:900px) and (orientation:landscape) and (max-height:500px){
 dialog{height:100dvh}
 .dlg-body{overflow-y:auto}
}

/* ---------- Add-event form: friendlier "Option B" styling ---------- */
.form label{text-transform:none;letter-spacing:0;font-size:12.5px;font-weight:600;color:#4a463f}
.form label i{opacity:.55}
.form input,.form select{border:1px solid #dcd8cf;border-radius:11px;background:#fff;padding:11px 13px;font-size:15px}
.form input:focus,.form select:focus{outline:none;border-color:var(--accent);box-shadow:0 0 0 3px rgba(31,59,255,.16)}
.form input::placeholder{color:#b3aea3}
.form .hint{font-size:12px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:5px;line-height:1.4;text-transform:none;letter-spacing:0}
.form button.primary{border-radius:11px;text-transform:none;letter-spacing:0;font-size:14px;font-weight:700;padding:14px 18px}
.form button.primary:hover{background:#1730d6;border-color:#1730d6;color:#fff}
/* the snap area becomes a soft, dashed "drop a flyer" panel */
.snap{display:block;margin-bottom:20px}
.snap-btn{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;width:100%;justify-content:flex-start;
  background:#fff;color:#4a463f;border:1.5px dashed #c7c2b8;border-radius:12px;
  padding:12px 15px;font-size:13.5px;letter-spacing:0;text-transform:none;font-weight:600;min-height:0}
.snap-btn::before{content:"📸";background:var(--accent);color:#fff;border-radius:9px;padding:7px 9px;font-size:15px;line-height:1}
.snap-btn:hover{background:#fff;border-color:var(--accent);color:var(--ink)}
.snap-msg{display:block;flex:none;font-size:12.5px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:8px;min-width:0}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="wrap">

<div class="hero">
  <div class="eyebrow">
    <span>Alpes-Maritimes · 06</span>
    <span><button type="button" class="linklike" id="about-open">About</button> · Updated <b>{{ updated }}</b></span>
  </div>
  <h1>What's<br>on in <em>Nice</em></h1>
  <div class="standfirst">
    <p>Vide-greniers and brocantes, milongas, jazz, club nights, museum shows,
       design and AI meetups, village fêtes and pop-ups — Nice and the coast,
       scraped daily from the sources that actually list them.</p>
    <div class="stats">
      <div class="stat"><b id="s-total">{{ stats.total }}</b><span>Listed</span></div>
      <div class="stat"><b id="s-week">0</b><span>Next 7 days</span></div>
      <div class="stat"><b>{{ stats.towns }}</b><span>Towns</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="marquee"><div class="marquee-inner" id="mq"></div></div>

<div class="bar">
  <input type="search" id="q" placeholder="Search title, venue, town, artist, DJ…">
  <select id="town"><option value="">All towns</option></select>
  <select id="when">
    <option value="">Any date</option>
    <option value="3">Next 3 days</option>
    <option value="7">Next 7 days</option>
    <option value="14">Next 14 days</option>
    <option value="30">Next 30 days</option>
    <option value="weekend">This weekend</option>
  </select>
  <label class="chk"><input type="checkbox" id="online"> Online too</label>
  <label class="chk"><input type="checkbox" id="freeonly"> Free only</label>
  <button id="reset">Reset</button>
</div>

<div class="cats" id="cats"></div>
<div class="tally" id="tally"></div>
<div id="list"></div>

<button class="addbtn" id="addbtn" aria-label="Add an event" title="Add an event">
  <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="square">
    <path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/>
  </svg>
</button>

<dialog id="dlg" aria-labelledby="dlg-title">
  <div class="dlg-head">
    <div>
      <h2 id="dlg-title">Add your event</h2>
      <p>Spotted a gap? Add it. A real person takes a look before it goes live.</p>
    </div>
    <button class="dlg-x" id="dlg-close" aria-label="Close">✕</button>
  </div>
  <div class="dlg-body">
  {% if submit_mode == 'none' %}
    <div class="callout" style="margin:0">
      <b>Submissions aren't wired up yet.</b> This site is static, so it can't receive a
      form post on its own. Set <code>SUBMIT_ENDPOINT</code> or <code>GITHUB_REPO</code>
      before building — see the README.
    </div>
  {% else %}
    <div class="callout">
      {# Only the endpoint mode has a file field, so don't promise a poster upload
         in the modes that don't offer one. #}
      <b>Add what's on.</b> Fill in the details. A real person takes a look before
      it goes live.
    </div>
    {# Snap-a-flyer: read a poster and prefill the form. With an AI endpoint
       configured (POSTER_AI_URL, or a deployed Supabase read-poster function) the
       photo is sent there to be read by a vision model; otherwise it's decoded
       on-device with OCR and never leaves the phone. Either way it's a rough
       first pass and every field stays editable. #}
    <div class="snap">
      <label class="snap-btn" for="s-photo">Snap or upload a flyer</label>
      {# No `capture` attribute: on a phone that forced the camera open and hid the
         photo library. Without it the browser offers both: take a photo OR pick
         an existing one from the album. #}
      <input type="file" id="s-photo" accept="image/*" hidden>
      <span class="snap-msg" id="snap-msg">Got a poster? We'll read it and fill in what we can, just check it after.</span>
    </div>

    <form class="form" id="sform"
          {% if submit_mode == 'endpoint' %}action="{{ submit_endpoint }}" method="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data"{% endif %}>
      {# Balanced two-per-row layout. Everything is required except Ends, Note and
         Link. Category is a <select> so it always has a value. #}
      <div class="f-full"><label for="s-title">Event name *</label><input id="s-title" name="title" required placeholder="e.g. Vernissage Jasmine"><div class="hint">The event's own name, not the venue.</div></div>
      <div class="f-half"><label for="s-date">Date *</label><input type="date" id="s-date" name="date" required></div>
      <div class="f-half"><label for="s-time">Time *</label><input type="time" id="s-time" name="time" required></div>
      {# Town is a datalist, not free text: start typing and matching towns
         appear, and submit rejects anything not already on the site. Keeps the
         town list clean, no "Nice ", "nice", "Nice06" variants to canonicalise
         later. The <option>s are filled from the live town list in JS. #}
      <div class="f-half"><label for="s-town">Town *</label>
        <input id="s-town" name="town" list="townlist" required autocomplete="off"
               placeholder="Start typing a town…">
        <datalist id="townlist"></datalist></div>
      <div class="f-half"><label for="s-venue">Venue *</label><input id="s-venue" name="venue" required></div>
      <div class="f-half"><label for="s-cat">Category *</label>
        <select id="s-cat" name="category">
          {% for k, v in categories.items() %}<option value="{{ k }}">{{ v }}</option>{% endfor %}
        </select></div>
      <div class="f-half"><label for="s-end">Ends <i>(optional)</i></label><input type="date" id="s-end" name="end"></div>
      <div class="f-full"><label for="s-email">Your email *</label><input type="email" id="s-email" name="email" required placeholder="you@email.com"><div class="hint">Just to confirm it's really you. Never shown on the site.</div></div>
      <div class="f-full"><label for="s-note">Note <i>(optional)</i></label><input id="s-note" name="note" placeholder="Price, what to expect…"></div>
      <div class="f-full"><label for="s-url">Link <i>(optional)</i></label><input id="s-url" name="url" placeholder="https://… a poster, Facebook event, venue page"><div class="hint">Handy proof, but not required.</div></div>
      {% if submit_mode == 'endpoint' %}
      <div class="f-full"><label for="s-img">Poster image (optional)</label><input type="file" id="s-img" name="poster" accept="image/*"></div>
      {% endif %}
      <div class="f-full" style="display:flex;gap:8px;align-items:center">
        <button class="primary" type="submit">Submit for review</button>
        <span id="smsg"></span>
      </div>
    </form>
  {% endif %}
  </div>
</dialog>

<dialog id="about-dlg" aria-labelledby="about-title">
  <div class="dlg-head">
    <div>
      <h2 id="about-title">About</h2>
      <p>A little passion project for Nice &amp; the 06.</p>
    </div>
    <button class="dlg-x" id="about-close" aria-label="Close">✕</button>
  </div>
  <div class="dlg-body about-body">
    <p>Hello! <b>What's on in Nice</b> is a little passion project, made by one
       person who loves this place and wanted all the good things happening around
       Nice and the Alpes-Maritimes gathered into one calm spot.</p>
    <p>Because it's all a bit scattered, isn't it? A poster in a café window, a
       Facebook event, a tourist-office page, a museum's own site. So every day
       this little site goes around, gathers it all up, tidies it, and always
       points you back to the lovely people actually putting things on.</p>
    <p>It's free, there are no ads, and every listing sends you to the source. Spot
       something missing? <b>Add it.</b> Nothing appears automatically; a real
       person gives new additions a friendly once-over first. And if you walk past
       a poster, just snap it and the site will try to fill in the details for you.</p>
    <p>A weekly email of what's new is on the way. Want to be first to get it?
       <a href="mailto:hello@whatsonnice.com?subject=Newsletter">Say hi</a> and
       you're on the list.</p>
    <p class="sign">Made with love in Nice. 💙</p>
  </div>
</dialog>

<div class="foot">
